==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gyron
<hw>Gy"ron</hw> <pr>(j⟦imac⟧"r⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>giron</ets>; of German origin. See <er>Gore</er> a piece of
cloth.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>A subordinary of triangular form
having one of its angles at the fess point and the opposite side at the
edge of the escutcheon. When there is only one gyron on the shield it is
bounded by two lines drawn from the fess point, one horizontally to the
dexter side, and one to the dexter chief corner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gyronny</ent>⟦br⟧
